<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10061391>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Habitus of examined specimens: (A, B) Nipponasellus sudzukhensis spec. nov., holotype X54657/Cr-2475-FEFU, male, 5.5 mm, dorsal view (A); lateral view (B). (C, D) Nipponasellus matsumotoi spec. nov., holotype X54659/Cr-2477-FEFU, male, 5.0 mm, dorsal view (C); lateral view (D)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10061391/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10061394>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Head features in dorsal, lateral, ventral and anterior oblique views (maxilliped removed): (A–D) Nipponasellus sudzukhensis spec. nov., paratype X54658/Cr-2476-FEFU, female, 5.0 mm; (E–H) Nipponasellus matsumotoi spec. nov., paratype X54660/Cr-2478-FEFU, female, 4.2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10061394/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10061381>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Height map of the Japanese continental margin arc system showing distribution of the genus Nipponasellus in East Asia, with position of the phreatic sampling sites. Each point may represent 1–3 closely adjacent localities (for further explanation, see text)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10061381/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10061396>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Nipponasellussudzukhensis spec.nov., holotype X54657/Cr-2475-FEFU, male,5.0 mm:(A) antennula; (B)antenna; (C) mandible, left; (D) mandible, right; (E) labium; (F) maxillula, with enlarged outer plate; (G) maxilla; (H) maxilliped." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10061396/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10061398>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Nipponasellus sudzukhensis spec. nov., holotype X54657/Cr-2475-FEFU, male, 5.0 mm: (A) pereopod 1, with enlarged palm; (B) pereopod 2; (C) pereopod 3; (D) pereopod 4; (E) pereopod 5; (F) pereopod 6; (G) pereopod 7." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10061398/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10061400>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Nipponasellus sudzukhensis spec. nov., holotype X54657/Cr-2475-FEFU, male, 5.0 mm: (A) pleotelson, ventral view (g.p., genital papilla); (B) pleopod 1; (C) pleopod 2, with schematic outline of details of appendix masculina; (D) pleopod 3; (E) pleopod 4; (F) pleopod 5; (G) uropod. Paratype X54658/Cr-2476-FEFU, female, 6.0 mm: (H) pleopod 2." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10061400/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10061402>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Scanning electron micrographs of pleopod 2 of Nipponasellus sudzukhensis spec. nov., adult male: (A) pair of pleopods 2, ventral view; (B) endopodite of pleopod 2, right; (C, D) appendix masculina enlarged, right and left." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10061402/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

